news.title: India Cements posts net loss of Rs 7 crore in Q3 FY24
news.para: Revenue from operations was at Rs 1,144.46 crore during the period under review. It was Rs 1,281 crore in the corresponding quarter a year ago.

news.title: ED searches India Cements offices in FEMA probe
news.para: The searches were launched on Wednesday at two office premises of the company in Chennai and one in Delhi, under the provisions of the Foreign Exchange Management Act (FEMA)

news.title: India's Prism Johnson posts a net profit of Rs 1.78 crore in Q3 FY 24
news.para: The cement and tiles maker said its net profit after tax came in at 17.8 million rupees ($214,537.96) for the quarter ended Dec. 31, compared to a loss of 447.4 million rupees in the year-earlier period. This was the company's fourth straight quarterly profit.

news.title: Interim Budget 2024: A roadmap for inclusive development and economic resilience
news.para: The budgetary measures strategically focus on key sectors such as urban and rural housing, infrastructure, and transportation, indicating a concerted effort to stimulate economic growth while addressing the diverse needs of society.

news.title: Karnataka government to digitise land records to check fraud deals
news.para: The initiative, Bhu Suraksha, is set to be launched within a month, starting with one taluk in each of the 31 districts, minister Krishna Byregowda said Wednesday. This strategic move, while ensuring transparency and efficiency in maintaining land records, will also allow easy accessibility to those records.

news.title: Government to launch scheme to help middle class buy or build own house: Finance minister
news.para: Parallely, she also announced building 2 crore more houses for the rural poor in the next five years under the continuing PM Awas Yojana (Grameen).

news.title: Country Garden looks to sell its $570 million residential development in London
news.para: Property agent Knight Frank said it had been appointed by Risland UK - a subsidiary of Country Garden - to market the 1,000-home Calico Wharf development, where construction has yet to start, in the Poplar area of the city.

news.title: Delhi HC pulls up MCD officials for failing to act against illegal construction
news.para: A bench headed by Acting Chief Justice Manmohan "warned" the officials, who were present in court, and questioned how the construction activity was permitted to go on in spite of an earlier order directing removal of illegal structures there as well as a 'work stop' notice.

news.title: Ludhiana development body seals 58 flats, evicts illegal occupants
news.para: In all, 82 houses had been identified where illegal occupants had been living. These occupants had been served eviction notices on July 27, 2023.

news.title: Patna civic body issues notices to 220 property tax defaulters
news.para: The notices served three months ago, will be taken into action from February 5 to 20. PMC has requested the Patna DM to provide additional police force for the action.

news.title: Pimpri Chinchwad civic body issues notices to 426 units for violating safety norms
news.para: The civic body has surveyed a total of 43,925 commercial properties to date in the ongoing survey. The officials have identified 2,423 commercial establishments, including 718 industrial units that are violating safety norms in the Talawade red zone and need immediate intervention to prevent any major fire mishaps.

news.title: Gurugram: Snag hits DTCP portal, holds up nod to building plans for three weeks
news.para: One of the flaws noticed by the department in the past few days is that the online system is charging for stilt plus four floors even if the applicant is constructing only three floors.

news.title: Goa: New property buyers to pay 2% of rate to housing co-operative society as premium
news.para: Out of the premium collected, housing societies will have to pay Rs 10,000 to government from the premium amount while transferring the shares and occupancy rights of a plot of land, housing unit or commercial unit.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body nets Rs 109.65 crore from two plots
news.para: On Wednesday, the civic body sold a commercial plot in Makarba Town Planning Scheme 26, measuring 6,657 sq metres for 1.51 lakh per sq metre against a base price of Rs 1.5 lakh.

news.title: Kajaria Ceramics' net profit up 40.2% in Q3 FY24
news.para: Kajaria Ceramics reported a consolidated net profit of 1.04 billion rupees ($12.5 million) in the quarter ended Dec. 31, compared to 743.2 million rupees a year ago.

news.title: Properties registrations in Mumbai municipal area may rise 21% in January: Report
news.para: Of the overall estimated registered properties, residential units constitute 80 per cent, and the remaining 20 per cent are non-residential assets.

news.title: HeidelbergCement India's net profit rises to Rs 31.47 crore in Q3
news.para: HeidelbergCement India's total revenue from operations was up 12.4 per cent to Rs 607.13 crore in the third quarter of the ongoing fiscal. It was Rs 540.12 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous fiscal.

news.title: House prices in United Kingdom beat forecasts as mortgage rates edge down
news.para: Nationwide said house prices in January increased by 0.7% from the month before after being flat in December, beating economists' forecast in a Reuters poll for a 0.1% rise.
